BIB                 12         25
INSTITUTE  (1USAORL)
REFERENCE  (J,NSE,77,146,1981)
           #doi:10.13182/NSE81-A21348
AUTHOR     (J.K.Dickens,J.W.McConnell, K.J.Northcutt)
TITLE      Yields of short-lived fission products produced by
            thermal-neutron fission of plutonium-239.
FACILITY   (REAC,1USAORL) Oak ridge research reactor
INC-SPECT  Thermal neutrons, flux of 5.0e13 neutrons/cm**2-sec
SAMPLE     (94-PU-239,ENR=0.999)
           1 microgram of Pu oxide, enriched to 99.9%
            Pu-239. Contained in polyethylene holder.
DETECTOR   (GELI) Shielded 50-cm**3 germanium-lithium detector.
            Efficiency measured with calibrated sources and
            checked with Ra-226 source.
METHOD     Measurements begun 35-secs after end of irradiation
            period. Comparison of measured yields to yields
            determined with a calibrated fission chamber used to
            determine the number of fissions.
MONITOR    No information
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by J.K.Dickens, 81/7/31.
           (TABLE,,J.K.Dickens+,J,NSE,77,146,1981) Table II, p.151
HISTORY    (19810513C)
           (20260110A) OS. STATUS information added, several BIB
            updates, minor correction in sub.2, converted to
            lower and upper case
ENDBIB              25
